description:
A multi-purpose stembolt with a fast seal-engaging mechanism.
Used in various technologies, such as reverse-racheting routing planers.
name: Self-Sealing Stem Bolt

description: A standard Starfleet-grade isolinear chip, formatted for data storage.
name: Isolinear Chip

description: Pieces of damaged and worn duranium hull sheeting.
name: Duranium Debris

description:
A common drinking stein used by Klingons.
It is stained with old bloodwine.
name: Klingon Drinking Stein

description: A mug from a standard replicator pattern used when ordering a regular raktajino.
name: Raktajino Mug

description: A Personal Access Display Device, unpowered and with a cracked screen.
name: Broken PADD

description: An alternative to transparent aluminum. Shatterproof, but damaged.
name: Cracked Duraglass

description: A bundle of specialized fiber-optic cabling used in ODN systems.
name: Opti-cable Bundle

description: A lone hypospray, missing its cylinder
name: Empty Hypospray

description: A pair of Tucker Tubes with its original platforming.
name: Tucker Tubes

description: A bar of solid parsteel.
name: Parsteel Bar

description: An empty standard issue Starfleet blue barrel.
name: Blue Barrel

description: A damaged power cell.
name: Fused Power Cell

description: A large standard-issue Starfleet electroplasma system manifold.
name: EPS Manifold

description: An empty secure fluid canister used on Starfleet vessels.
name: Fluid Canister

description: A copper spiralled conduit reinforced and insulated with a nanopolymer sheath.
name: Nanopolymer Conduit

description: A modern plasma relay.
name: Plasma Relay

description: A pair of old coils.
name: Warp Coils

description: A strong alloy used in generations of Starfleet ships.
name: Tritanium Bulkhead

description: Stray pieces of noranium alloy sheet metal.
name: Noranium Scrap

description: A highly traded commodity used for the construction of many things.
name: Magnesite Ore

description: A rare mineral that produces electric discharges, but can be refined to regulate it.
name: Gallicite Nodule

description:
A radiolytic mineral that has many applications when properly refined.
Commonly used for trade but regulated by the Federation.
name: Raw Kemocite

description: Volatile in its raw form, uridium alloy was commonly used in Cardassian construction.
name: Uridium Alloy

description: A generic graviton displacing sled used to transport items.
name: Anti-Grav Lift

description: A compact and mobile disk that inhibits transporter signals.
name: Transporter Inhibitor

description:
A pattern enhancer. Usually used in a set of 3 for triangulation.
Links to annular confinement beams to allow transporting in certain conditions.
name: Pattern Enhancer

description:
A component used to regulate power from the warp core to secondary systems.
Used in many Starfleet vessels and more.
name: EPS Step-Down Node

description: A gemstone so worthless that it's lack of popularity has made it a rarity.
name: Lobi Crystal

description:
A universally used energy regulator.
Useful for trade as almost every spacefaring species requires it.
name: Dilithium Crystals

description:
A small growth of rare benamite crystals.
They are used to regulate slipstream drives.
name: Benamite Cluster

description: A common Cardassian data-storage alternative to Federation Starfleet isolinear chips.
name: Isolinear Rod

description: A small wooden statuette, representing fertility on the planet Risa.
name: Horga'hn

description: A toxic and volatile waste product produced by Starfleet warp cores.
name: Trilithium Resin

description: A rare Cardassian gemstone, used in ancient times as ornate accoutrements.
name: Jevonite Gem

description: A lightweight crystalline mineral with distinct black streaks.
name: Promethean Quartz

description: A strong material used to build ground fortifications.
name: Riddinite Brick

description: A ceramic alloy used in spacecraft construction by some pre-warp species.
name: Talgonite Tile

description: A soft mineral substance with remarkable botanical properties.
name: Zenite Cylinder

description:
A compound that serves as insulation against Delphic-type spatial distortions.
Has neurotoxicant effects on vulcanoid species.
name: Trellium Ore

description:
A crystalline dendrite of chimerium, a highly valuable mineral.
Used in Klingon cloaking devices, as well as chimeric cloaks.
name: Chimerium Dendrite

description:
A small compressed chemical tablet that is a contact combustive.
Used as an emergency light and heat source.
name: Magnasite-Nitron Tablet

description: A long-lasting inertial guidance system used on many starships.
name: Tricellite Guidance System

description:
A genetically engineered high-yield perennial grain.
Used on many Federation colonies.
name: Quadrotriticale

description: An empty Starfleet Medical biohazard container.
name: Biohazard Container

description: Rocket-propelled boots allowing the user to reach new heights.
name: Levitation Boots

description:
A variable compound used to create a hard physical shell around specimens.
Used for quarantine as an added measure beyond energy fields.
name: Styrolite Coater

description: An attachable chest module used by Benzites unable to breathe standard M-Class atmospheres
name: Benzite Breather

description: A cultural icon for Bajorans, it represents familial ties and the wearer's D'jarra.
name: Bajoran Earring

description: An inert Borg nanoprobe.
name: Inert Nanoprobe

description: A small headset used by members of the Dominion in lieu of a viewscreen.
name: Virtual Sensory Display

description: An environmental helmet worn by the elusive Breen species.
name: Breen Helmet

description: An addictive narcotic isogenic enzyme used by the Dominion to control Jem'Hadar footsoldiers.
name: Ketracel-White Vial

description: Ground up dried beetles used as a stimulant by Ferengi.
name: Hupyrian Beetle Snuff

description: The black box data recorder of a Starfleet vessel.
name: Starship Black Box

description: A Starfleet engineering tool.
name: Hyperspanner

description:
A small device invented by Starfleet Science that emits polaron radiation.
This disrupts Changelings' morphogenic matrix.
name: Polaron Emitter

description: A container capable of precise atmospheric control for holding volatile samples.
name: Volatile Containment Module

description:
An isotopic device that allowed for long range tracking of a subject.
Both internal and external application is possible.
name: Viridium Tracker

description: A Visual Instrument and Sensory Organ Replacement used by those hard of seeing.
name: VISOR

description: A powerful liquid substance capable of dissolving duranium.
name: Magnasite Dropper

description: A radioactive Vulcan mineral used for tracking and cosmetic purposes.
name: Vokaya Amulet

description: An old obsolete piece of 22nd century equipment.
name: Horonium Alloy

description: A chest full of marriage gifts with an animatronic face used by Betazoids
name: Betazoid Gift Box

description: A guidebook for players of Bat'leths and BiHnuchs.
name: BnB Player's HandPADD

description: An unlabelled rare piece of Starfleet equipment.
name: Space Fun Helmet

description:
A small headset with a cone and disk game with addictive neurological effects.
This addictive version is outlawed.
name: Ktarian Game

description: An exceedingly rare write-once read-only Cardassian isolinear rod.
name: Optolythic Data Rod

description:
The iconic bucket first used by Constable Odo on DS9. 
These buckets were also used by Great Divide infiltrators in 2401
name: Changeling Bucket

description:
A physical bound hard copy of the Rules of Acquisition.
Issued by the Ferengi Government, for a fee
name: Rules of Acquisition

description: A complete set of a three dimensional chess game.
name: 3-D Chess Set

description: Fake Ferengi prosthetic lobes.
name: Fake Lobes

description: A glowing cube that melds with the user's body with unpredictable side effects based on emotion.
name: Ataxian Mood Shifter

description: A container of highly unstable protomatter.
name: Protomatter Container

description: A rare egg sculpture.
name: Faberg Egg

description: A small bottle of 17 million SHU hot sauce.
name: Ketracel White-Hot Sauce

description: A small bottle of bubble bath liquid in the shape of Lieutenant Commander Data.
name: Data Bubble Bath

description: A neural activity controller capable of brainwashing a victim.
name: Ferengi Thought Maker

description: An illegal form of interrogation used by the Tal Shiar.
name: Romulan Mind Probe

description:
A device employed by the Terran Empire in interrogation.
Developed based on recovered schematics from cross-overs.
name: Memory Extractor

description:
A small highly controlled and refined version of the Genesis Device.
Used for colonization and terraforming.
name: Miniature Genesis Device

description:
A device found on an abandoned lab developed by an unknown alien race.
Capable of assassinating anyone in range from behind closed doors.
name: Tantalus Field

description: A device recovered from the Mirror Universe used to inflict pain as punishment.
name: Terran Agonizer

description:
A highly destructive cascading biogenic pulse generator which destroys all organic matter within a range.
Developed by the Tal Shiar during the Dominion War.
name: Mini Thalaron Generator

description: A recreation of an ancient Vulcan weapon that serves as a psionic resonator.
name: Stone of Gol

description: Replica of the staff carried by the head of the Ferengi Alliance.
name: Replica Scepter of the Grand Nagus

description: A highly volatile substance that can create black holes when provoked.
name: Red Matter Canister

description: Highly volatile refined kemocite ore, which has many useful purposes.
name: Refined Kemocite

description: A wrappage of yamok sauce.
name: Yamok Sauce

description: A versatile organic gel used for both bio-neural circuitry and bioweapons.
name: Bio-Mimetic Gel

description: Built by a race driven to extinction by itself, the EP-607 was a sophisticated anti-personnel and spaceborne drone.
name: Echo Papa 607

description: A sophisticated portal weapon developed by the Daystrom Institute.
name: Portal Weapon

description:
One of several standardized testing objects used for various things, such as testing transporters.
Comprised of duranium alloy, duraglass, and a nonvolatile power source.
name: Starfleet Test Cylinder

description: A tank of deuterium gas.
name: Deuterium Gas

description:
A regulating cell with a benamite core.
Required to use a ship's slipstream drive.
name: Slipstream Cell

description: Test
name: Test
